        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 4 at 8:24PM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 822 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers along a line
extending from near Plymouth to near Chenango Bridge. Movement was
east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 35 mph.

SOURCE...Measured on the weather station at BGM airport.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Norwich, Sidney, Guilford, Edmeston, Plymouth, North Norwich,
Coventry, Greene, Oxford, and Pittsfield.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
